snippet: Among those killed on Monday was Ricardo Tochimani, but his name appears on no list of storm casualties. It stands alone, a homicide, and the identity of his killers remains a mystery.
abstract: Michael Wilson Crime scene column notes that among those killed during Hurricane Sandy was Ricardo Tochimani of Brooklyn, but his name appears on no list of storm casualties; it stands alone, a homicide that took place in the middle of the night outside a Bensonhurst bar as the storm bore down on New York; identity of Tochimani's killers remains a mystery.
lead_paragraph: Among those killed on Monday was Ricardo Tochimani, but his name appears on no list of storm casualties. It stands alone, a homicide, and the identity of his killers remains a mystery.
